The paper discusses the algorithmic framework of Approximate Message Passing (AMP) for solving linear inverse problems from noisy measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions applications such as reconstructing images and audio, which fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenge of large-scale processing, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC).
